Description: Wall sherd of East Greek (North Ionian?) pottery cup or bowl; brown clay with some silver mica; interior: dark brown glaze; reserved exterior save a black band on lower wall; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of Apollo (Naukratis), temenos (said to be)
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.366)
